# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Dashboard — Bloque 3 environment variables
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in real values.
# .env.local is gitignored and must never be committed.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─── Supabase (cloud hosted project) ──────────────────────────
# Get these from: https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/<ref>/settings/api
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT-REF.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=REPLACE_WITH_ANON_KEY
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=REPLACE_WITH_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY

# ─── OpenClaw Gateway (single source of truth) ────────────────
# OpenClaw 2026.4.5 running locally on Javier's Mac Mini.
# HTTP base is used by server-side route handlers only.
# WebSocket URL is exposed to the browser for the pixel world subscriber.
OPENCLAW_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:18789
NEXT_PUBLIC_OPENCLAW_WS_URL=ws://127.0.0.1:18789

# ─── Ed25519 device identity (optional override) ──────────────
# Leave blank on first boot — the client auto-generates a keypair
# and persists it in localStorage. Set this to a hex-encoded
# 32-byte seed if you want deterministic device identity across
# browsers (not recommended for production).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DEVICE_SEED=
